Caption: Fig. 2. Illustration of a second stream monitoring system using a Human Oracle. In this system, the machine samples the stream (left), performs an initial filtering step to screen out unambiguous samples (center), and passes each remaining sample through to the Human Oracle (right). Such a system is most effective in scenarios when the number of sam- ples that could be screened out is relatively large.
